== 社群 ==

開放原始碼社群使用Discord<ref name="discord-tweet">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/comma_ai/status/1084955002118889472|title=comma ai on Twitter: "Moving from Slack to Discord"|website=Twitter.com|publisher=Comma.ai, Inc.|accessdate=2019-02-27}}</ref>與[[GitHub|GitHub]]來支援開發。

comma.ai已釋出工具與指南協助開發者支援他們的汽車<ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/@comma_ai/how-to-write-a-car-port-for-openpilot-7ce0785eda84|title=How to write a car port for openpilot|first=comma|last=ai|date=2018-08-04|website=Medium|accessdate=2020-08-06|archive-date=2020-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805235311/https://medium.com/@comma_ai/how-to-write-a-car-port-for-openpilot-7ce0785eda84|dead-url=no}}</ref>。另外，他們也釋出了可以讓使用者審閱他們的駕駛過程的工具<ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/@comma_ai/the-half-way-point-55662cef04f2|title=The Half Way Point|first=comma|last=ai|date=2018-07-13|website=Medium|accessdate=2020-08-06|archive-date=2020-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818004519/https://medium.com/@comma_ai/the-half-way-point-55662cef04f2|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== 分支 ===
comma.ai維護openpilot的程式碼與釋出版本，並且也有不斷成長中的社群維護openpilot的各種分支。這些分支多具有各種實驗性功能，如煞車燈偵測等。

未有自動駕駛的Tesla型號也有社群分支來支援其改裝<ref>{{cite web|url=https://community.comma.ai/wiki/index.php/Tesla|title=Tesla - comma wiki|website=community.comma.ai|accessdate=2020-08-06|archive-date=2019-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190227182036/https://community.comma.ai/wiki/index.php/Tesla|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。克萊斯勒與吉普的部份車型也透過社群貢獻而得以支援<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/comma_ai/status/1091550019151220736|title=Giraffe for FCA group released! openpilot now officially supports only the Chrysler Pacifica Hybrid, but it will soon spread to all Chrysler, Jeep and Fiat with ACC and LaneSense!https://comma.ai/shop/products/giraffe#&gid=1&pid=9 …|date=2019-02-01|access-date=2020-08-06|archive-date=2021-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210630124112/https://twitter.com/comma_ai/status/1091550019151220736|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/adhintz/openpilot|title=adhintz/openpilot|website=GitHub|accessdate=2020-08-06|archive-date=2020-09-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200907010517/https://github.com/adhintz/openpilot|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

